rdf:Description.rdfs:label: directDownload
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the dataset is publicly available and can be downloaded directly.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasStaticLink
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element statically links in each `to` Element, during a LifecycleScopeType period.
An Element an annotator has made an assertion about.
Specifies the CVSS base, temporal, threat, or environmental severity type.
An SPDX version 2.X compatible verification method for software packages.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha512
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SHA-2 with a digest length of 512, as defined in [RFC 6234](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc6234).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: design
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A relationship has specific context implications during an element's design.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: complete
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The relationship is known to be exhaustive.
Specifies the value of the content identifier.
Portion of an AnyLicenseInfo representing this version, or any later version, of the indicated License.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: blake3
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [BLAKE3](https://github.com/BLAKE3-team/BLAKE3-specs/blob/master/blake3.pdf)
A value used in a CdxExtension name-value pair.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: falcon
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [FALCON](https://falcon-sign.info/falcon.pdf)
A License participating in a 'with addition' model.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: data
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Element is data
Specifies a time when a vulnerability assessment was modified
Provides an EPSS assessment for a vulnerability.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasDocumentation
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element is documented by each `to` Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: source
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SBOM created directly from the development environment, source files, and included dependencies used to build an product artifact.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ai
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the AI profile specification

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: development
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A relationship has specific context implications during development phase of an element.
Contains a URL where the License or LicenseAddition can be found in use.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasTest
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is a test artifact for the `from` Element (`from` hasTest `to`), during a LifecycleScopeType period.
Provides an indication of where to retrieve an external Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: module
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a module of a piece of software

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: securityPolicy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to instructions for reporting newly discovered security vulnerabilities for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: registration
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the dataset is not publicly available and an email registration is required before accessing the dataset, although without an affirmative acceptance of terms.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: certificationReport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a certification report for a package from an accredited/independent body.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: cpe22
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [Common Platform Enumeration Specification 2.2](https://cpe.mitre.org/files/cpe-specification_2.2.pdf)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: secureSoftwareAttestation
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to information assuring that the software is developed using security practices as defined by [NIST SP 800-218 Secure Software Development Framework (SSDF) Version 1.1](https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/218/final) or [CISA Secure Software Development Attestation Form](https://www.cisa.gov/resources-tools/resources/secure-software-development-attestation-form).
A concrete subclass of AnyLicenseInfo used by Individuals in the ExpandedLicensing profile.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: testedOn
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (AI, Dataset) The `from` Element has been tested on the `to` Element(s).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: componentAnalysisReport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a Software Composition Analysis (SCA) report.
Specifies the amount of energy consumed when finetuning the AI model that is being used in the AI system.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: republishedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (Security) Designates a `from` Vulnerability's details were tracked, aggregated, and/or enriched to improve context (i.e. NVD) by each `to` Agent.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: inlineMitigationsAlreadyExist
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Built-in inline controls or mitigations prevent an adversary from leveraging the vulnerability.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Used when the type does not match any of the other options.
Describes the preprocessing steps that were applied to the raw data to create the given dataset.
A license exception that is listed on the SPDX Exceptions list.
Provide consumers with comments by the creator of the Element about the Element.
A short description of an Element.
Provides a CVSS version 2.0 assessment for a vulnerability.
Records if sensitive personal information is used during model training or could be used during the inference.
Specifies an AI package and its associated information.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasDeclaredLicense
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Software Artifact was discovered to actually contain each `to` license, for example as detected by use of automated tooling.
Provides a reference to a resource outside the scope of SPDX-3.0 content that uniquely identifies an Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: availableFrom
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element is available from the additional supplier described by each `to` Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: noSupport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: there is no support for the artifact from the supplier, consumer assumes any support obligations.
Identifies the full text of a License, in SPDX templating format.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: bom
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Element is a bill of materials
Specifies a data package and its associated information.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: audio
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data is audio based, such as a collection of music from the 80s.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha224
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SHA-2 with a digest length of 224, as defined in [RFC 3874](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc3874).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: configures
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element is a configuration applied to each `to` Element, during a LifecycleScopeType period.
Describes the type of the given dataset.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: archive
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is an archived collection of one or more files (.tar, .zip, etc)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: swhid
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SoftWare Hash IDentifier, persistent intrinsic identifiers for digital artifacts. The syntax of the identifiers is defined in the [SWHID specification](https://www.swhid.org/specification/v1.1/4.Syntax) and in the case of filess they typically look like `swh:1:cnt:94a9ed024d3859793618152ea559a168bbcbb5e2`.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: mavenCentral
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a Maven repository artifact. The artifact locator format, looks like `groupId:artifactId[:version]`, is defined in [Maven documentation](https://maven.apache.org/guides/mini/guide-naming-conventions.html).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasAssessmentFor
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (Security) Relates a `from` Vulnerability and each `to` Element(s) with a security assessment. To be used with `VulnAssessmentRelationship` types.
A buildType is a hint that is used to indicate the toolchain, platform, or infrastructure that the build was invoked on.
A map of Element identifiers that are used within a Document but defined external to that Document.
A collection of Elements, not necessarily with unifying context.
Provides information about the creation of the Element.
A distinct article or unit related to Software.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: executable
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Element is an Artifact that can be run on a computer
Abstract class representing a License or an OrLaterOperator.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: releaseHistory
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a published list of releases for a package.
An SPDX Element containing an SPDX license expression string.
Specifies the SPDX License List version in which this license or exception identifier was deprecated.
A license expression participating in a license set.
Records the time when a recommended action was communicated in a VEX statement to mitigate a vulnerability.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: socialMedia
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a social media channel for a package.
A buildId is a locally unique identifier used by a builder to identify a unique instance of a build produced by it.
Asbtract ancestor class for all VEX relationships
Describes a mechanism to update the dataset.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: model
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a machine learning or artificial intelligence model
Specifies the CVSS qualitative severity rating of a vulnerability in relation to a piece of software.
An Individual Value for Element representing a set of Elements with cardinality (number/count) of zero.
Specifies the type of the external identifier.
Specifies whether the License is listed as free by the [Free Software Foundation (FSF)](https://fsf.org).
Agent represents anything with the potential to act on a system.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: securityThreatModel
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference the [security threat model](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Threat_model) for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: md4
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: MD4 message-digest algorithm, as defined in [RFC 1186](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc1186).
A license that is listed on the SPDX License List.
A license that is not listed on the SPDX License List.
Describes a relationship between one or more elements.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: altDownloadLocation
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to an alternative download location.
Specifies the time from which an element is no longer applicable / valid.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: serializedInArtifact
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` SPDXDocument can be found in a serialized form in each `to` Artifact.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A relationship has other specific context information necessary to capture that the above set of enumerations does not handle.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: System Package Data Exchange (SPDX) Ontology
rdf:Description.dcterms:abstract: This ontology defines the terms and relationships used in the SPDX specification to describe system packages
rdf:Description.dcterms:creator: SPDX Project
rdf:Description.dcterms:title: System Package Data Exchange (SPDX) Ontology

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Specifies the time an artifact was built.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: framework
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a software framework
Provides an exploit assessment of a vulnerability.
Provides additional purpose information of the software artifact.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: securityOther
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to related security information of unspecified type.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: securityAdvisory
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a published security advisory (where advisory as defined per [ISO 29147:2018](https://www.iso.org/standard/72311.html)) that may affect one or more elements, e.g., vendor advisories or specific NVD entries.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: simpleLicensing
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the simple Licensing profile specification
Base domain class from which all other SPDX-3.0 domain classes derive.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: cpe23
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [Common Platform Enumeration: Naming Specification Version 2.3](https://csrc.nist.gov/publications/detail/nistir/7695/final)
Uniquely identifies an external element.
A canonical, unique, immutable identifier
Describes one a profile which the creator of this ElementCollection intends to conform to.

Provide the enumeration of possible decisions in the [Stakeholder-Specific Vulnerability Categorization (SSVC) decision tree](https://www.cisa.gov/stakeholder-specific-vulnerability-categorization-ssvc).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: diskImage
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element refers to a disk image that can be written to a disk, booted in a VM, etc. A disk image typically contains most or all of the components necessary to boot, such as bootloaders, kernels, firmware, userspace, etc.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: runtime
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SBOM generated through instrumenting the system running the software, to capture only components present in the system, as well as external call-outs or dynamically loaded components. In some contexts, this may also be referred to as an "Instrumented" or "Dynamic" SBOM.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: high
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: When a CVSS score is between 7.0 - 8.9
An Individual Value for Element representing a set of Elements of unknown identify or cardinality (number).
Specifies the version of a VEX statement.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: vulnerableCodeCannotBeControlledByAdversary
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The vulnerable component is present, and the component contains the vulnerable code. However, vulnerable code is used in such a way that an attacker cannot mount any anticipated attack.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: altWebPage
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to an alternative web page.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: describes
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element describes each `to` Element. To denote the root(s) of a tree of elements in a collection, the rootElement property should be used.
Provides a NamespaceMap of prefixes and associated namespace partial URIs applicable to an SpdxDocument and independent of any specific serialization format or instance.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasHost
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Build was run on the `to` Element during a LifecycleScopeType period (e.g. the host that the build runs on).

Abstract class representing a license combination consisting of one or more licenses (optionally including additional text), which may be combined according to the [SPDX license expression syntax](../../../annexes/SPDX-license-expressions.md).
A license or addition that is not listed on the SPDX License List.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: clickthrough
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the dataset is not publicly available and can only be accessed after affirmatively accepting terms on a clickthrough webpage.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: green
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Dataset can be shared within a community of peers and partners.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasVariant
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is a variant the `from` Element (`from` hasVariant `to`).
Abstract class for the portion of an AnyLicenseInfo representing a license.
Provides the location of an exploit catalog.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: low
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: When a CVSS score is between 0.1 - 3.9

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: vcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a version control system related to a software artifact.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: timeseries
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data is recorded in an ordered sequence of timestamped entries, such as the price of a stock over the course of a day.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: md6
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [MD6 hash function](https://people.csail.mit.edu/rivest/pubs/RABCx08.pdf)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: endOfSupport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: there is a defined end of support for the artifact from the supplier. This may also be referred to as end of life. There is a validUntilDate that can be used to signal when support ends for the artifact.

Property that describes the time at which a build stops.
Specifies the SSVC decision type.
Provides an independently reproducible mechanism that permits verification of a specific Element.
Provides an IntegrityMethod with which the integrity of an Element can be asserted.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha256
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SHA-2 with a digest length of 256, as defined in [RFC 6234](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc6234).
Provide an enumerated set of lifecycle phases that can provide context to relationships.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: vulnerableCodeNotPresent
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The product is not affected because the code underlying the vulnerability is not present in the product.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: evidence
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is the evidence that a specification or requirement has been fulfilled
The version of the SPDX License List used in the license expression.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: core
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the Core profile specification
Describe that a CVE is known to have an exploit because it's been listed in an exploit catalog.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: releaseNotes
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to the release notes for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: fixedIn
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (Security/VEX) A `from` Vulnerability has been fixed in each of the `to` Element(s). The use of the `fixedIn` type is constrained to `VexFixedVulnAssessmentRelationship` classed relationships.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha3_256
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SHA-3 with a digest length of 256, as defined in [FIPS 202](https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/fips/202/final).
Specifies the amount of energy consumed when training the AI model that is being used in the AI system.
Capture the scope of information about a specific relationship between elements.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: noAssertion
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: No assertion can be made about the completeness of the relationship.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: staticAnalysisReport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a static analysis report for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: noAssertion
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Makes no assertion about the field.
Provides the location for more information regarding an external identifier.
Defines the original host file that the snippet information applies to.
The name of a relevant standard that may apply to an artifact.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: issueTracker
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to the issue tracker for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasMetadata
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is metadata about the `from` Element (`from` hasMetadata `to`).
A reference to a resource outside the scope of SPDX-3.0 content related to an Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: test
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A relationship has specific context implications during an element's testing phase, during development.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: source
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a single or a collection of source files
A mapping between prefixes and namespace partial URIs.
Identify the version of a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: configuration
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Element is configuration data

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: bower
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a Bower package. The package locator format, looks like `package#version`, is defined in the "install" section of [Bower API documentation](https://bower.io/docs/api/#install).
A characterization of some aspect of an Element that is associated with the Element in a generalized fashion.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: exportControlAssessment
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a export control assessment for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasProvidedDependency
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element has a dependency on each `to` Element, dependency is not in the distributed artifact, but assumed to be provided, during a LifecycleScopeType period.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Other exploit catalogs
Describes potentially noisy elements of the dataset.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: contains
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element contains each `to` Element.
The field describes the availability of a dataset.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasConcludedLicense
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Software Artifact is concluded by the SPDX data creator to be governed by each `to` license.
Identifies the full text of a LicenseAddition.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: exploitCreatedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (Security) The `from` Vulnerability has had an exploit created against it by each `to` Agent.
A software agent.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: high
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The second-highest level of risk posed by an AI system.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: buildSystem
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference build system used to create or publish the package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: securityAdversaryModel
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to the security adversary model for a package.
Portion of an AnyLicenseInfo representing a License which has additional text applied to it.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: syntactic
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data describes the syntax or semantics of a language or text, such as a parse tree used for natural language processing.
Abstract class for additional text intended to be added to a License, but which is not itself a standalone License.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: device
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element refers to a chipset, processor, or electronic board

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: dataset
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the Dataset profile specification
Provides a CVSS version 3 assessment for a vulnerability.
Provides information about the creation of the Element.
Provides a set of values to be used to describe the common types of SBOMs that tools may create.
A distinct article or unit within the digital domain.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: cwe
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [Common Weakness Enumeration](https://csrc.nist.gov/glossary/term/common_weakness_enumeration). A reference to a source of software flaw defined within the official [CWE List](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/) that conforms to the [CWE specification](https://cwe.mitre.org/).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: structured
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data is stored in tabular format or retrieved from a relational database.
A type of extension consisting of a list of name value pairs.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: attend
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The vulnerability requires attention from the organization's internal, supervisory-level individuals. Necessary actions include requesting assistance or information about the vulnerability, and may involve publishing a notification either internally and/or externally. CISA recommends remediating Attend vulnerabilities sooner than standard update timelines.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: generates
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element generates each `to` Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: support
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the artifact has been released, and is supported from the supplier. There is a validUntilDate that can provide additional information about the duration of support.
Identifies when the Element was originally created.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: chat
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to the instant messaging system used by the maintainer for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: file
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a single file which can be independently distributed (configuration file, statically linked binary, Kubernetes deployment, etc)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: deployed
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: in addition to being supported by the supplier, the software is known to have been deployed and is in use. For a software as a service provider, this implies the software is now available as a service.
A collection of SPDX Elements describing a single package.
Specifies a vulnerability and its associated information.
Describes the confidentiality level of the data points contained in the dataset.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: foundBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (Security) Designates a `from` Vulnerability was originally discovered by the `to` Agent(s).
An Individual Value for License where the SPDX data creator determines that no license is present.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: mailingList
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to the mailing list used by the maintainer for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: library
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a software library

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: software
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the Software profile specification

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: securityOther
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Used when there is a security related identifier of unspecified type.
Specifies the level of support associated with an artifact.
Identifies the full text of a License or Addition.
Portion of an AnyLicenseInfo representing a set of licensing information where all elements apply.
Specifies the time when a vulnerability was published.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: componentNotPresent
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The software is not affected because the vulnerable component is not in the product.
A property name with an associated value.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: megajoule
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Megajoule.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: security
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the Security profile specification
Specifies an Extension characterization of some aspect of an Element.
Provides a CVSS version 4 assessment for a vulnerability.
Provides information about the content type of an Element or a Property.
Describes if any sensitive personal information is present in the dataset.
Describes if a given file is a directory or non-directory kind of file.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: incomplete
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The relationship is known not to be exhaustive.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: vulnerabilityDisclosureReport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a Vulnerability Disclosure Report (VDR) which provides the software supplier's analysis and findings describing the impact (or lack of impact) that reported vulnerabilities have on packages or products in the supplier's SBOM as defined in [NIST SP 800-161 Cybersecurity Supply Chain Risk Management Practices for Systems and Organizations](https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/161/r1/final).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: none
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: When a CVSS score is 0.0

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: critical
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: When a CVSS score is between 9.0 - 10.0

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: qualityAssessmentReport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a quality assessment for a package.
An Individual Value for License when no assertion can be made about its actual value.
A tuple of two positive integers that define a range.
A reference to a resource identifier defined outside the scope of SPDX-3.0 content that uniquely identifies an Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: analyzed
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SBOM generated through analysis of artifacts (e.g., executables, packages, containers, and virtual machine images) after its build. Such analysis generally requires a variety of heuristics. In some contexts, this may also be referred to as a "3rd party" SBOM.
Defines the line range in the original host file that the snippet information applies to.
The class that helps note down the quantity of energy consumption and the unit used for measurement.
Specifies the amount of energy consumed during inference time by an AI model that is being used in the AI system.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: medium
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The third-highest level of risk posed by an AI system.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: specification
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a plan, guideline or strategy how to create, perform or analyse an application
A container for a grouping of SPDX-3.0 content characterizing details (provenence, composition, licensing, etc.) about a product.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: firmware
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element provides low level control over a device's hardware
Records any relevant background information or additional comments about the origin of the package.
Provides advise on how to mitigate or remediate a vulnerability when a VEX product is affected by it.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: build
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SBOM generated as part of the process of building the software to create a releasable artifact (e.g., executable or package) from data such as source files, dependencies, built components, build process ephemeral data, and other SBOMs.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Any other units of energy measurement.
Links a vulnerability and one or more elements designating the latter as products not affected by the vulnerability.
A collection of SPDX Elements that could potentially be serialized.
Defines the end of a range.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasInputs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Build has each `to` Elements as an input, during a LifecycleScopeType period.
Describes all the preprocessing steps applied to the training data before the model training.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: categorical
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data that is classified into a discrete number of categories, such as the eye color of a population of people.
A collection of Elements that have a shared context.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: gitoid

A gitoid of type blob is a unique hash of a binary artifact. A gitoid may represent either an [Artifact Identifier](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-identifier-types) for the software artifact or an [Input Manifest Identifier](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#input-manifest-identifier) for the software artifact's associated [Artifact Input Manifest](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-input-manifest); this ambiguity exists because the Artifact Input Manifest is itself an artifact, and the gitoid of that artifact is its valid identifier. Gitoids calculated on software artifacts (Snippet, File, or Package Elements) should be recorded in the SPDX 3.0 SoftwareArtifact's contentIdentifier property. Gitoids calculated on the Artifact Input Manifest (Input Manifest Identifier) should be recorded in the SPDX 3.0 Element's externalIdentifier property. See [OmniBOR Specification](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/), a minimalistic specification for describing software [Artifact Dependency Graphs](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-dependency-graph-adg).
